-- In SQL, the UNION operator selects fields from two or more tables but it does not include duplicates.
-- In SQL, the UNION ALL operator selects fields from two or more tables but it includes duplicates.

-- The SQL UNION and UNION ALL with the WHERE clause
select age, name 
from Teachers
where age >= 20
union all
select age, name 
from students
where age >= 20

Challenge
Suppose you are working as a backend engineer at an e-commerce company that maintains a table named Customers. The schema of this table is as follows:
it has two columns Customer_id and Customer_name
Write a query that gets the missing id,s;
Logic = Generate all ids - Existing ids
WITH RECURSIVE all_ids AS (
    SELECT MIN(customer_id) AS id, MAX(customer_id) AS max_id
    FROM Customers
    UNION ALL
    SELECT id + 1, max_id
    FROM all_ids
    WHERE id < max_id
)
SELECT id AS missing_id
FROM all_ids
WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT customer_id FROM Customers)
ORDER BY id;
